payment_info.1.player.feedback_text: Interesting.  Now I get the feeling that I'm not playing against another person.  Basically what happens is I choose one that matches what they put.  So the next few times we choose the same name.  And then for no apparent reason other than maybe to screw me up (why would anyone need to do that) they choose a different name.  On the first time doing that, I understand.  What I did when I played before was I chose a different name because I thought I had to, but then it didn't match, so then I chose one that did.  But when it comes to this time, each time I used the same name, they would put a different name.  So it's making me think that, you, the requester set us players against a computer to see what we'd do when they changed names.  In any case it's no problem, still a fun hit.
